Hypothesis: Chimpanzee could learn sign lang, think and reason like humans
	Ethical and moral issues of captive and research animals
	Bonds between animal and human

Stephanie Lafarge (psych student): Teaches Nim like he was human child, american sign lang
	Nim learns quickly, becomes media attention
Nim gets harder to handle (aggressive, unpredictable behavior)
	Returned to lab for further experimentation
